headline: Invesco’s Senior Loan ETF Owns Some Of Elon Musk’s X Debt Yielding 10% | BKLN
summary: The Invesco Senior Loan ETF (NYSEARCA:BKLN) generates income by investing in floating-rate senior secured loans made to below-investment-grade companies, typically rated single-B. These loans sit at the top of a borrower’s capital structure with first claim on assets in bankruptcy, providing protection versus unsecured bonds or equity.
